Credit Line: The Jefferson R. Burdick Collection, Gift of Jefferson R. Burdick
Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History: The United States and Canada, 1800–1900 A.D.
Description: Trade cards from the "Actresses (Folder Series)" (N96), issued in a set of 25 cards ca. 1889 to promote Honest Long Cut Tobacco, manufactured by W. Duke Sons & Co. Each card has two side panels that were designed to fold over the center panel.
